Biography|id=Richardson_Archibald}}</ref>
==Career== Richardson collaborated with [[Dudley E. Littlewood]] on invariants and group representation theory. They introduced [[the immanant of a matrix]], studied [[Schur polynomial|Schur functions]] and developed the [[Littlewood–Richardson rule]] for their multiplication.
==Awards and honours== Richardson was elected a [[Fellow of the Royal Society]]<ref name="frs"/> on 21 March 1946.
